<HL>
   McDermott Unit Gets Contract
</HL>
<DATE>
04/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   FTX MDR FRP
</CO>
<IN>
COMMODITY MARKETS FOR METALS (MIN)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW ORLEANS -- McDermott Marine Construction, a unit of
McDermott International Inc., received a $250 million
contract to design and build 15 offshore sulfur-mining
platforms for Freeport-McMoRan Resource Partners.
   Freeport-McMoRan Resource Partners is a limited
partnership and an affiliate of Freeport-McMoRan Inc.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The platforms are to be installed in the Gulf of Mexico,
off the coast of Louisiana. The contract also calls for
construction of 13 bridges, a power-plant module and related
facilities. Fabrication will be at McDermott's fabrication
yards in Bayou Boeuf and New Iberia, La., as well as at the
company's Gulfport, Miss., shipyard.
</TEXT>
